*GIVEAWAY* How does rest fuel your creativity? When @hatchforsleep reached out to me to paint one of their restore 2 devices and give it away to one of my loyal followers, I jumped at the chance. I’ve been a @hatchforsleep customer for years. I used their devices to help sleep train my toddlers and help them learn when it was time to sleep and ok to wake. @hatchforsleep is in the business to help you and your loved ones get the best, quality sleep to help you recuperate and slay your day! 

Being a mother of three, a wife, and painter, I find that rest is absolutely essential. Without it, there’s not much left to give. Do yourself a favor and get a Restore 2 device. I promise you’ll be glad you did!! Pink noise is my favorite. 

To enter the giveaway, follow @hatchforsleep and @lauren.smith.art and comment with how you refuel. Every comment is a separate entry so tag your friends too!

In the 11/15 RELEASE with @wellandwonder I am including a few classics for those of you who swoon over a neutral palette 🎨 🤎🤍🩶

Oaks exude history and strength and that’s why I and so many people are drawn to them. In the South, we have the most beautiful oaks with long wide limbs that have lived for over a century. If you plant a new young oak, they grow slow. They are something for future generations to enjoy in maturity. But you plant them knowing you’ll never live long enough to see them in their full glory and you plant them anyway.  Because you know someone one day will stand and stare at their glory and appreciate that someone who came before loved them enough to do it. 

I am offering semi custom paper pieces for two days. You choose the color combination that speaks to you from the ones I have shown and you choose the number of trees you want. There are many things the trees can represent, marriage, birth, parents and children, grandparents and grandchildren, friendships, friend groups or any other sentiment that fits the bill. They also just look cool so don’t overthink it!!

DM me for your order. 🌳🌳🌳
